@startuml UC-04_Execute_Workflow_Sequence

title UC-04: Execute Workflow - Sequence Diagram

skinparam SequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam SequenceArrowColor #D32F2F
skinparam ActorBackgroundColor #FFEBEE
skinparam ParticipantBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam SequenceGroupBackgroundColor #FFF9C4

actor Trigger
participant ExecutionEngine
participant ExecutionService
participant Database as DB
participant WorkflowService
participant IntegrationService
participant ErrorHandler
participant AnalyticsService

Trigger -> ExecutionEngine: 1. Workflow Trigger Event
note right of Trigger
  Trigger Types:
  • Manual execution
  • Scheduled
  • Webhook
  • Third-party event
end note

ExecutionEngine -> ExecutionService: 2. start_execution(workflow_id, trigger_data)

ExecutionService -> DB: 3. Fetch Workflow
activate DB
DB --> ExecutionService: 4. Workflow object
deactivate DB

ExecutionService -> DB: 5. Create Execution Record
activate DB
DB --> ExecutionService: 6. execution_id
deactivate DB

ExecutionService -> ExecutionService: 7. Initialize execution_context

ExecutionEngine --> Trigger: 8. execution_id (async response)

ExecutionService -> ExecutionService: 9. Get first node (trigger)
ExecutionService -> ExecutionService: 10. Execute node

loop For Each Step
    ExecutionService -> WorkflowService: 11. Get step configuration
    WorkflowService -> DB: 12. Query step config
    DB --> WorkflowService: 13. Config data
    WorkflowService --> ExecutionService: 14. Step details
    
    ExecutionService -> IntegrationService: 15. execute_api_call(integration, endpoint, params)
    
    alt API Call Successful
        IntegrationService --> ExecutionService: 16. Return response data
        ExecutionService -> DB: 17. Log step execution
        activate DB
        DB --> ExecutionService: 18. Logged
        deactivate DB
        
        ExecutionService -> ExecutionService: 19. Evaluate conditions on edges
        ExecutionService -> ExecutionService: 20. Determine next step
    else API Call Failed
        IntegrationService --> ExecutionService: 16. Error response
        ExecutionService -> ErrorHandler: 17. handle_error(error, context)
        
        note right of ErrorHandler
          Error Classification:
          • Classify by severity
          • Check retry policy
          • Decide action
        end note
        
        ErrorHandler --> ExecutionService: 18. {retry: true, delay: 5s}
        ExecutionService -> ExecutionService: 19. Wait 5 seconds
        ExecutionService -> IntegrationService: 20. Retry API call (exponential backoff)
        
        alt Retry Succeeds
            IntegrationService --> ExecutionService: 21. Success
            ExecutionService -> ExecutionService: 22. Continue
        else Max Retries Exceeded
            ExecutionService -> ErrorHandler: 23. Log fatal error
            ErrorHandler -> DB: 24. Update execution status = "failed"
            DB --> ErrorHandler: 25. Updated
            ExecutionService -> AnalyticsService: 26. Track failure event
            AnalyticsService -> DB: 27. Store event
            DB --> AnalyticsService: 28. Stored
            ExecutionService --> Trigger: 29. Error notification sent
        end
    end
end

ExecutionService -> ExecutionService: 30. All steps completed

ExecutionService -> DB: 31. Update execution status = "success"
activate DB
DB --> ExecutionService: 32. Updated
deactivate DB

ExecutionService -> DB: 33. Record end_time & duration
activate DB
DB --> ExecutionService: 34. Updated
deactivate DB

ExecutionService -> AnalyticsService: 35. Track execution completion
AnalyticsService -> DB: 36. Store analytics event
activate DB
DB --> AnalyticsService: 37. Stored
deactivate DB

ExecutionService -> DB: 38. Increment workflow execution_count
activate DB
DB --> ExecutionService: 39. Updated
deactivate DB

ExecutionService --> ExecutionEngine: 40. Return {status: "success", logs: [...]}

ExecutionEngine -> Trigger: 41. Send completion notification

@enduml
